    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1903-11-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1903-11-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="244"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d244">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Ehrman</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Panama</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-11-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 10, 1903</hi>.</date>
                        <lb/>(Received 1.35 p.m.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Federico Boyd, a member of the Committee of the Government, Amador Guerrero, both
                    delegates, on the way to Washington to arrange in satisfactory manner to the
                    United States the canal treaty and other matters. Pablo Arosemena, attorney,
                    proceeds next steamer. English steamers were not held at Buenaventura. Gunboat
                        <hi rend="italic">Bogotá</hi> has left Buenaventura.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Ehrman.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
